<div class="page-header d-print-none">
  <div class="row align-items-center">
    <div class="col">
      <h2 class="page-title">
        Audit logs
        <span class="badge bg-yellow-lt ms-2">EXPERIMENTAL · BITEMPORAL</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="text-secondary">
        Demonstrates NodeDB v0.3.0's <code>BITEMPORAL</code> collection
        modifier surfaced through the adapter's new
        <code>create_collection ..., bitemporal: true</code>. Writes
        flow through ActiveRecord; reads bypass the model and unwrap
        the raw <code>{data,id}</code> blob shape returned by NodeDB
        v0.3.0 (BUG-018 territory). Once upstream projects virtual
        columns out, this controller can collapse to plain AR queries.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="alert alert-danger d-flex align-items-start mt-3">
  <i class="ti ti-alert-triangle me-2 mt-1"></i>
  <div>
    <strong>Bitemporal read path is broken upstream — table will stay empty.</strong>
    NodeDB v0.3.0 accepts the <code>CREATE COLLECTION … BITEMPORAL</code>
    DDL and INSERTs through ActiveRecord <em>appear</em> to succeed,
    but every form of SELECT (plain, scoped, <code>AS OF SYSTEM TIME NOW()</code>,
    <code>AS OF SYSTEM TIME &lt;ms&gt;</code>) returns zero rows. This
    demo ships to exercise the new
    <code>create_collection ..., bitemporal: true</code> surface and
    document the gap — it is not a working audit log today. Tracked
    upstream as BUG-021 (filed alongside this PR).
    See <a href="https://github.com/mkhairi/activerecord-nodedb-adapter/issues/45">issue #45 (BUG-018)</a>
    for the closely-related <code>{data,id}</code> blob projection
    issue on non-bitemporal native reads. <code>AS OF SYSTEM TIME</code>
    is not wired into AR Relation; raw SQL only when upstream lands
    the read path.
  </div>
</div>

<%= form_with url: audit_logs_path, method: :post, local: true, class: "card mt-3" do |f| %>
  <div class="card-body">
    <div class="row g-2">
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <%= f.label :actor, class: "form-label" %>
        <%= f.text_field :actor, class: "form-control", placeholder: "user@example.com" %>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <%= f.label :action_name, "Action", class: "form-label" %>
        <%= f.text_field :action_name, class: "form-control", placeholder: "viewed" %>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <%= f.label :target, class: "form-label" %>
        <%= f.text_field :target, class: "form-control", placeholder: "/articles/42" %>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <%= f.label :context, class: "form-label" %>
        <%= f.text_field :context, class: "form-control", placeholder: "{}" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="card-footer text-end">
    <%= f.submit "Record audit entry", class: "btn btn-primary" %>
  </div>
<% end %>

<div class="card mt-3">
  <div class="card-header">
    <h3 class="card-title">Recent entries</h3>
    <div class="text-secondary small ms-auto"><%= @logs.size %> rows · post-unwrap</div>
  </div>
  <div class="table-responsive">
    <table class="table table-vcenter card-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Recorded at</th>
          <th>Actor</th>
          <th>Action</th>
          <th>Target</th>
          <th>Context</th>
          <th>Document id</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <% @logs.each do |log| %>
          <tr>
            <td class="text-secondary small"><%= log[:recorded_at] %></td>
            <td><%= log[:actor] %></td>
            <td><span class="badge bg-blue-lt"><%= log[:action] %></span></td>
            <td><code><%= log[:target] %></code></td>
            <td class="text-secondary small"><code><%= log[:context] %></code></td>
            <td class="text-secondary small"><code><%= log[:id] || log[:_blob_id] %></code></td>
          </tr>
        <% end %>
        <% if @logs.empty? %>
          <tr>
            <td colspan="6" class="text-secondary text-center">
              Empty — INSERTs are accepted but reads return zero rows
              (NodeDB v0.3.0 bitemporal read-path bug, tracked as BUG-021).
              Try the standard non-bitemporal collections in the sidebar
              for working CRUD demos.
            </td>
          </tr>
        <% end %>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
